==Description==
{{Blurimage|file=c6f57caa40eb545d1d8ced13edf53821.jpg|caption=<span style="color: white">𝚏𝚒𝚐 1.0 First ever photo of '''Level 115'''.</span>}}
'''Level 115''', also known as "Preternatural Geometry," is believed to be an endless, labyrinthine complex of roofless rooms and hallways, all made from ceramic tiles covered in an abstract purple-green pattern. The space is populated with a variety of architectural features, including stairs, pillars, windows, and other seemingly random structures. Rooms connect through large, empty doorways, which vary in number—some rooms may have several doors, while others have only one. Dead ends are also common. The entire area has a brutalist aesthetic, with rooms that are generally large but empty, causing some wanderers to say they feel disorientation and confusion. This is aided by the similarity of the rooms, making them hard to distinguish from one another at first glance. Additionally, the layout seems to shift and rearrange itself when it’s not being looked at.

Surrounding the main complex is an endless void that resembles a pastel purple sky, with some areas tinged in shades of blue. It’s unclear if this is a real sky or simply an artificial "skybox." However, it is known that falling into this void results in the person vanishing completely within seconds. Because of this, it's strongly advised to stay away from the edges. As a wanderer approaches a ledge, they may begin to feel dizzy and have blurred vision. This effect can also be triggered by staring too intently at the cloud-like formations within the sky. The cause of these sensations remains unknown.
{{Blurimage|file=5c3e5d1a15c8748c9ad5c17244966f93.jpg|caption=<span style="color: white">𝚏𝚒𝚐 2.0 Newer image of '''Level 115'''.</span>|align=left}}
Throughout '''Level 115''', one can find gravity-defying, reflective metallic spheres often accompanied by a slimy purple liquid. Although these spheres appear metallic, they are weightless, floating as if filled with air. Prolonged contact with one of these spheres can cause numbness in the area touching it, eventually rendering that part unresponsive until contact is broken. Staring into the spheres’ reflections reveals a warped, distorted version of oneself. Prolonged observation induces feelings of dread and guilt over unknown actions. It is strongly advised not to look into these reflections for too long, as doing so can lead to a lasting sense of depression.

The purple liquid is often found in pool-like depressions in the floor, hovering just above the void yet inexplicably defying gravity. It has a viscous, slimy texture but behaves like regular water when it interacts with the metallic spheres. Consuming this liquid is strongly discouraged, as it can cause severe side effects, including brain development issues, memory loss, schizophrenia, depression, dementia, and other mental disorders. Additionally, it can lead to intense stomach pain.
{{Blurimage|file=74cbde838ec57277d7acc71fa5bca7d0.jpg|caption=<span style="color: white">𝚏𝚒𝚐 3.0 Unconfirmed photo of '''Level 115'''.</span>}}
This level has an isolating effect, making it difficult for wanderers to meet or stay together. Upon entering '''Level 115''', wanderers are spawned hundreds of kilometers apart, even if they entered from the same place at the same time. Additionally, when someone comes close to another wanderer, they experience a strong sense of unease and an instinctive urge to turn back and walk away. This feeling, combined with the shifting layout of the level, makes it nearly impossible for people to connect with one another here.

Aside from the metallic spheres and purple liquid, '''Level 115''' is completely devoid of any other objects or supplies, making it barren and desolate. It is highly recommended to bring sufficient supplies when entering this level, as there are none to be found here. Dehydration and starvation are one of the most common causes of death, making the level's emptiness one of its greatest dangers. Strangely, no corpses remain in the level; instead, they appear to be mysteriously absorbed into the floor after a period of time.

== Colonies & Outposts ==
Due to the nature of '''Level 115''' and the overall lack of incentive, no colonies or outposts have been established. The lack of supply, shifting geometry and environment and impracticality of sustaining any settlement make such efforts unnecessary.

== Entities ==
Given the conditions of '''Level 115''', no entities can survive here for prolonged periods, resulting in the complete absence of entities. Some wanderers claim that if one places their ear close to one of the metallic spheres they might hear a heartbeat, though this phenomenon is generally believed to be a symptom of encroaching insanity.

== Entrances & Exits ==
__NOTOC__

=== Entrances ===

* Finding a metallic sphere in [[Level 114]] and noclipping through it will result in the wanderer waking up here.
* Denting any wall from throwing a bowling ball on [[Level 499]] will bring one here.
* You may randomly end up here by touching random metal patches on the ground in [[Level 833]].

=== EXITS ===

* When looking into the reflection of the metallic sphere one might suddenly feel very nostalgic, this will cause them to end up in [[Level 165]].

